      • doBenchmarkQuery

        public void doBenchmarkQuery(java.lang.String server,
                             java.util.List<java.lang.String> tsdbQueryList)
        This method is used to actually benchmark the given TSDBs on a given server. If there is no benchmark generated meta data in the BenchmarkTimeSeriesMetaDataDirectoryPath this method will generate random time series meta data from previously imported time series which will then be stored in BenchmarkTimeSeriesMetaDataDirectoryPath. So for future calls all TSDBs are measured with the same set of meta data. The QueryFunction and percentile value will be selected randomly for every set of meta data but will be the same per set for all TSDBs per measurement, of course.
        Parameters:
        server - the address or ip on which the query should be performed.
        tsdbQueryList - the TSDBs on which the query should be performed.

      • queryWithFunction

        Performs queries with given meta data and function on all tsdbs on given server.
        Parameters:
        server - the server address or ip
        queryID - the unique queryID
        metaDataList - the meta data on which the queries should be performed.
        function - the query function that should be performed.
        p - the percentile value (if needed, null if not).
        tsdbQueryList - list of tsdbNames which should be queried.
        Returns:
        list of answers from the server.
